Params: {1: 'Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgStory/Bgstory54.jpg'}
{3: 'On the other side, Roland, who has just received the evacuation order, is expressing his doubts to his companions.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Roland', 3: 'Why did this end so quickly?', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "This whole situation is too bizarre. It wouldn't have ended this fast even with Luna on the field herself.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: "Don't you believe in Miss Luna's power?", 4: '2'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "No, if this was a full frontal assault, no one would've been able to stand up to her.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "But this was not the case. People would've hid and fled in all directions. It would've taken some time to find them if she was just by herself.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: 'Just like Lamia—', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lamia', 3: 'Hey—! Why are you bringing me into this?', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Roland', 3: 'When you went taking care of the Babylonian squad who were searching for "that thing," didn\'t it take you a whole day to get back?', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lamia', 3: 'B-because there was a Construct hiding...', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Roland', 3: 'See my point? This whole situation is strange.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: "What's peculiar about a snatch and grab?", 4: '2'}
{3: 'Not wanting to continue the conversation with Roland, Gabriel turns to leave. Likewise, Lamia recedes back into the shadows.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Roland', 3: 'What I mean is—', 4: '1'}
{3: 'Even so, Gabriel cannot get rid of Roland.'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "If it was just me and you, what would've happened?", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: "We take what Miss Luna wanted and leave. That's all.", 4: '2'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: 'Exactly. "That\'s all."', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: 'Infiltrate the Route Union, take what we wanted, and leave. All without alerting anyone of our presence.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "If Miss Luna wanted to destroy the Route Union, she would've done it more thoroughly.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "She's left so many people alive, each person could be trouble down the line.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "Luna's actions couldn't have been for a mission... Understand?", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "Not to mention, this isn't the first time she's held back.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "It's just like last time. She had Alpha sparing that guy instead of killing him as if that'd scare him straight. And then what happened?", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: 'What are you trying to say?', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: 'Would a qualified agent leave loose ends like this?', 4: '1'}
{3: 'Gabriel musters up a sneer through his vocalizer covered in heavy cloth and continues walking forward, despite Roland standing in the way.'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "Hey, where do you think you're going?", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: 'Preparations need to be made.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: 'Really? Need a hand?', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: "That won't be necessary. It's just some trivial matters.", 4: '2'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "Nonsense. You've been unusually busy recently. You must be up to something big.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: 'If you want to complain about not having enough work, just spit it out already.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: "No, no. That's not what I meant.", 4: '1'}
{3: "Seeing Roland's persistence, Gabriel stops in his tracks."}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: 'It\'s "feeding" time.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: 'Huh? You sure seem attached to it.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: "Someone who talks to skeletons everyday says I'm attached?", 4: '2'}
{3: "Unable to see Gabriel's face behind his metal face mask, Roland felt a mixture of delight and contempt from him."}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: "Now it's the only thing I care about.", 4: '2'}
{2: 'Gabriel', 3: "Humanity's worst nightmare has finally come to life. We must see to it that raise it right.", 4: '2'}
{1: 'Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgStory/Bgstory55.jpg'}
{1: '1', 2: 'α', 3: 'You seem irritated.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'α', 3: '"Stupid things as always" wouldn\'t make you have that expression. Does it have anything to do with what Huaxu showed you?', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Luna', 3: '...The institute brought back some memories from my past.', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 3: 'Alpha remains silent for a moment. Obviously, she knows what Luna meant by her past.'}
{2: 'α', 3: "It's now in ruins.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'α', 3: "I understand why you feel this way, but that wasn't the smartest course of action.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Luna', 3: "You don't need to worry about me, Sister.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Luna', 3: 'No one can shake the power of Ascnet. Not as one person. Not as a group.', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'α', 3: "I wouldn't state the obvious.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'α', 3: "Destroying that institute can't change the past. It will only affect your mood.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'α', 3: 'Do you want to do something for them?', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Luna', 3: 'I only did what I wanted to do.', 4: '1'}
{3: 'Luna hovers over her sister and gazes off at the ruins in the distance.'}
{2: 'Luna', 3: 'I\'m not interested in seeking justice for those "sinners."', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Luna', 3: "I'm only interested in uprooting all that I hate.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Luna', 3: "No matter if my actions benefit others, they will never thank me. But, I've never sought humanity's gratitude.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Luna', 3: "I only do what I want to do. And that's all I'll ever do.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'α', 3: '...Apologies. I always seem to infer the current situation according to how you used to think as a child.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Luna', 3: 'Nothing wrong with habits brought about by memories, Sister.', 4: '1'}
